cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper is about achieving work conserving bandwidth guarantees in multi-tenant data centers, which involves network infrastructure and system design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses data center management and resource allocation, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The solution proposed in the paper involves dynamic binding of tenants to queues, which could be considered a control system, placing it under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses security concerns related to multi-tenant data centers, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper proposes a solution that is implementable on existing switching chips, which could fall under cs.PF (Performance).
